body: Feather color in eagles is regulated by two genes, A and B. The A gene follows an autosomal dominant inheritance pattern, where the dominant phenotype denotes a green coloration and the recessive phenotype denotes a gold coloration. Furthermore, the B gene epistatically regulates the A gene where the presence of the dominant B allele is required to express feather coloration, otherwise the eagle will be albino. If two eagles heterozygous for both genes are crossed, what is the probability the offspring will have gold feathers?

Which of the following best describes the magnitude of work done by friction on a rolling object?

choices.W: Nonzero for rolling with slipping, nonzero for rolling without slipping
choices.X: Nonzero for rolling with slipping, zero for rolling without slipping
choices.Y: Zero for rolling with slipping, nonzero for rolling without slipping
choices.Z: Zero for rolling with slipping, zero for rolling without slipping

answer: X) Nonzero for rolling with slipping, zero for rolling without slipping

When calculating the speed of sound in a solid, the Young's modulus of the solid is used, but when calculating speed of sound in a liquid, the bulk modulus is used instead. Which of the following best explains why this is the case?

choices.W: Liquids are much less dense than solids
choices.X: Liquids flow laterally under stress while solids do not
choices.Y: Liquids have nonlinear stress-strain curves while solids do not
choices.Z: Liquids compress adiabatically while solids compress isothermally

answer: X) Liquids flow laterally under stress while solids do not
